headline: MCD's International Markets Stay Resilient: What's Supporting Comps?
summary: McDonald's leans on resilient international markets as disciplined value, local marketing and scale efficiencies help support comps amid global QSR pressure.

headline: McDonald’s Upgraded, Netflix Downgraded: Updated Rankings on Top Blue-Chip Stocks
summary: During these busy times, it pays to stay on top of the latest profit opportunities. And today’s blog post should be a great place to start. After taking a close look at the latest data on institutional buying pressure and each company’s fundamental health, I decided to revise my Stock Grader recommendations for 125 big blue chips. headline: Domino's Shares Jump After Merrill Pereyra Named Australia, New Zealand CEO
summary: Domino's Pizza Enterprises shares rose as much as 6.8% after appointing fast-food veteran Merrill Pereyra to lead Australia and New Zealand operations.
